      "source": [
        "Step 2: Load and Preprocess Data\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "sXqLjy1kJv03"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Load the dataset\n",
        "file_path = \"/content/Training.csv\"  # Ensure correct file path\n",
        "df = pd.read_csv(file_path)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Replace hyphens with NaN\n",
        "df = df.replace('-', np.nan)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Drop missing values\n",
        "df = df.dropna()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Select features and target\n",
        "features = ['Open', 'High', 'Low']\n",
        "target = ['Close']\n",
        "\n",
        "X = df[features].values\n",
        "y = df[target].values\n",
        "\n",
        "# Normalize data\n",
        "scaler_X = MinMaxScaler()\n",
        "scaler_y = MinMaxScaler()\n",
        "\n",
        "X_scaled = scaler_X.fit_transform(X)\n",
        "y_scaled = scaler_y.fit_transform(y)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Train-Test Split (80% training, 20% testing)\n",
        "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_scaled, y_scaled, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Reshape for LSTM (samples, timesteps, features)\n",
        "X_train = np.reshape(X_train, (X_train.shape[0], 1, X_train.shape[1]))\n",
        "X_test = np.reshape(X_test, (X_test.shape[0], 1, X_test.shape[1]))"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mUg5akkUJ06q"
      },
      "execution_count": 2,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Define Bi-LSTM + TimesNet Model (Optimized)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kyZA16KfKMU3"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def build_optimized_model(lstm_units=128, dense_units=128, dropout_rate=0.3, learning_rate=0.001):\n",
        "    input_layer = Input(shape=(1, X_train.shape[2]))  # (timesteps, features)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Bi-LSTM Layer with Dropout Regularization\n",
        "    bi_lstm_layer = Bidirectional(LSTM(lstm_units, return_sequences=False,\n",
        "                                        dropout=dropout_rate, recurrent_dropout=dropout_rate))(input_layer)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # TimesNet Branch (Dense Layer)\n",
        "    timesnet_layer = Flatten()(input_layer)\n",
        "    timesnet_layer = Dense(dense_units, activation='relu')(timesnet_layer)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Merge Layers\n",
        "    merged_layer = Concatenate()([bi_lstm_layer, timesnet_layer])\n",
        "    merged_layer = Dropout(dropout_rate)(merged_layer)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Output Layer\n",
        "    output_layer = Dense(1, activation='linear')(merged_layer)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Compile Model with Adam Optimizer\n",
        "    model = Model(inputs=input_layer, outputs=output_layer)\n",
        "    model.compile(optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=learning_rate), loss='mse', metrics=['mae'])\n",
        "\n",
        "    return model"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "We_vWvfcKNMq"
      },
      "execution_count": 3,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Hyperparameter Optimization Using Bayesian Search"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "7UdTKJcoKS7w"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Define the search space for hyperparameters\n",
        "search_space = [\n",
        "    Integer(64, 256, name='lstm_units'),  # LSTM units\n",
        "    Integer(64, 256, name='dense_units'),  # Dense units\n",
        "    Real(0.2, 0.4, name='dropout_rate'),  # Dropout rate\n",
        "    Real(0.0001, 0.01, name='learning_rate'),  # Learning rate\n",
        "    Integer(16, 64, name='batch_size')  # Batch size\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Function to minimize error using Bayesian optimization\n",
        "def objective(params):\n",
        "    lstm_units, dense_units, dropout_rate, learning_rate, batch_size = params\n",
        "    model = build_optimized_model(lstm_units, dense_units, dropout_rate, learning_rate)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Train the model with early stopping and learning rate decay\n",
        "    history = model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=30, batch_size=batch_size,\n",
        "                        validation_split=0.2, verbose=0,\n",
        "                        callbacks=[EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=5, restore_best_weights=True),\n",
        "                                   ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_loss', factor=0.5, patience=3)])\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Return the validation loss (MSE)\n",
        "    val_loss = min(history.history['val_loss'])\n",
        "    return val_loss\n",
        "\n",
        "# Perform Bayesian Optimization\n",
        "best_params_bayes = gp_minimize(objective, search_space, n_calls=10, random_state=42)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Best hyperparameters after optimization\n",
        "print(f\"Best Hyperparameters: LSTM Units={best_params_bayes.x[0]}, Dense Units={best_params_bayes.x[1]}, \"\n",
        "      f\"Dropout Rate={best_params_bayes.x[2]}, Learning Rate={best_params_bayes.x[3]}, Batch Size={best_params_bayes.x[4]}\")\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {

        "outputId": "b46fed7b-bf00-4752-fd39-c68466ac221d"

          ]
        }
      ]
    },
